    diagnostics: ['In-lab polysomnography showing central apneas (absent airflow AND absent respiratory effort)', 'Central AHI >=5 events/hour with associated symptoms', 'Echocardiography to assess cardiac function', 'BNP/NT-proBNP', 'Brain MRI if brainstem pathology suspected', 'Medication review for opioids/CNS depressants', 'Arterial blood gas for awake hypercapnia'],
